    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Feature description\r\n\r\nWith the new _cmdheight=0_ feature (#1004) the `recording @*` indicator for macros is not visible anymore.\r\nThis makes recording macros less intuitive and possibly leads to confusion when _q_ is hit by accident.\r\n\r\nI think a good solution would be to expand the command line as long as the macro is being recorded and close it again afterwards.",
    "closed_at": "2024-02-11T12:08:46Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "You can use `reg_recording()` to show the register in your 'statusline'. But I also think we should do the following:\r\n\r\n# Proposal\r\n\r\n- âœ…  change `SHM_RECORDING` (`shortmess=q`) so that it actually shows nothing. The current behavior of `shortmess=q` is pointless. \r\n    - done: #27415\r\n    - with this option , we can remove the `!ui_has_messages()` check in `recording_mode`. Then users decide whether to set shortmess=q. ",
