            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> I think a good solution would be to expand the command line as long as the macro is being recorded and close it again afterwards.\r\n\r\nIt is complex.  Because neovim needs to save the state and restore it later.\r\nI think `ext_messages` should support the behavior.\r\n\r\n> with this option , we can remove the !ui_has_messages() check in recording_mode. Then users decide whether to set shortmess=q.\r\n\r\nIt is possible.  But it does not fix the problem...\r\n\r\n> This makes recording macros less intuitive and possibly leads to confusion when q is hit by accident.",
