        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I used Shougo's above suggestion and I also see the bug that causes 'recording @' to fail to appear. For me\r\nIt never shows up a second time, but I found a nonsensical work around that allows 'recoding @' to always appear.\r\n\r\n```\r\nautocmd(\"RecordingEnter\", {\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    vim.opt.cmdheight = 1\r\n    -- neovim 9:\r\n    -- The below vim.notify allows the 'recording @' message to show up if used more than once. if using cmdheight=0\r\n    vim.notify(\"this does nothing\", vim.log.levels.OFF, {\r\n    })\r\n  end\r\n})\r\n```",
