        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> change SHM_RECORDING (shortmess=q) so that it actually shows nothing. The current behavior of shortmess=q is pointless. \r\n\r\nCan this be done? It's kinda annoying when you have a statusbar using `reg_recording()` and want to use cmdheight=1.\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n static void recording_mode(int attr)\r\n {\r\n-  msg_puts_attr(_(\"recording\"), attr);\r\n   if (shortmess(SHM_RECORDING)) {\r\n     return;\r\n   }\r\n\r\n-  char s[4];\r\n-  snprintf(s, ARRAY_SIZE(s), \" @%c\", reg_recording);\r\n+  char s[13];\r\n+  snprintf(s, ARRAY_SIZE(s), \"recording @%c\", reg_recording);\r\n   msg_puts_attr(s, attr);\r\n }\r\n```",
